column8: This spreadsheet includes everybody who has been a member since November 1st, 2014, whether or not they are still a member today.
If the same person has had multiple accounts, or has opened and closed the same account multiple times:

column9: If this person has an open account as of June 2017, these dates are for the *longest continuously open account which is still open today*
If this person does not have an open account as of June 2017, these dates are for the *most recently closed account*

column8: All latitudes and longitudes are randomized within 400 metres of the home address on file.

column9: The randomization knows it's on a sphere: you don't have to do any weird corrections based on lines of longitude being shorter near the poles.
The randomization knows it's in a circle: it is unbiased towards the centre of the circle.
The randomization is consistent: the same hash and home address will always produce the same latitude and longitude.

column8: All dates are truncated to the 1st of the month.
